tent":"2 g","fatContent":"46 g","servingSize":"Serves 4","unsaturatedFatContent":"0 g"},"recipeCategory":["Entree","Dinner","Mains","Quick Dinners"],"recipeCuisine":["Mexican","Tex-Mex"],"recipeIngredient":["For the Salsa:","5 radishes, diced","1/2 fennel bulb, diced (plus some fronds, if you have them)","2 scallions, white and pale-green parts only, thinly sliced","1/2 cup (20g) cilantro leaves and tender stems, chopped","1/2\u00a0jalape\u00f1o pepper, seeds removed if desired, finely chopped","2 tablespoons (30ml) fresh juice from 1 lime","Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper","For the Quesadillas:","1 tablespoon (15ml) extra-virgin olive oil, divided, plus more as needed","8 ounces (225g) Spanish-style chorizo sausage (cured, not fresh), cut into 1/2-inch cubes","4 (8-inch) flour tortillas","2 cups mixed grated cheddar and pepper Jack cheeses (8 ounces; 225g), divided (see note)","2 scallions, thinly sliced"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"For the Salsa: In a medium bowl, toss together radishes, fennel (plus fronds, if using), scallions, cilantro, jalape\u00f1o, and lime juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"For the Quesadillas: In a large cast iron skillet or on the flat side of a cast iron griddle, heat 1/2 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat until lightly smoking. Add chorizo and cook until browned, turning once, about 3 minutes. Remove from pan with a slotted spoon onto a paper towel\u2013lined plate."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Set out 4 tortillas on a work surface and sprinkle approximately 1 ounce (28g) cheese over half of each tortilla. Scatter chorizo and scallions on top of cheese, then top with remaining cheese. Fold tortillas in half over filling to form a half-moon shape."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add remaining 1/2 tablespoon oil to skillet or griddle and heat over medium-high heat until lightly smoking."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add quesadillas to skillet or griddle in a single layer, working in batches if necessary. Cook until lightly browned, about 4 minutes. Flip quesadillas and cook until second side is crisp and cheese is fully melted, about 3 minutes. Add more oil as needed if working in batches. While cooking any remaining batches, keep finished quesadillas warm by arranging them on a baking sheet in a single layer and holding them in a 250\u00b0F oven."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cut quesadillas into wedges and serve with radish and fennel salsa."}],"recipeYield":"4","totalTime":"PT20M","review":[{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"awineguy"},"reviewBody":"\"To save time, you can use pre-shredded cheese.\"\n\n\nHow much time does it take to grate 2 cups of cheese, 1 minute maybe 2 ? Hardly seems worth it to add cellulose to your diet."},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Michael Gilbert"},"reviewBody":"The quesadillas were a big hit, but, no nutrition data is a disappointment."},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sircrunchalot"},"reviewBody":"So good! I used fresh Mexican chorizo as it is available from my local butcher shop. The fennel-radish salsa is the bomb dot com. I will be making it for chorizo tacos, etc. Served with 'Broiled Asparagus with Cotija Cheese' (link below). \n\nhttp://www.seriouseats.com/broiled-asparagus-with-cotija-cheese-recipe"},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"kathi t"},"reviewBody":"The radish fennel cilantro adds a fascinating flavor plus crunch. Love it."},{"@type":"Review","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"LarBear"},"reviewBody":"Made these last week; they were great. Love another excuse to use Spanish chorizo."}],"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":["WebPage"],"@id":"https://www.seriouseats.com/chorizo-quesadillas-radish-fennel-salsa-recipe","breadcrumb":{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@id":"https://www.seriouseats.com/all-recipes-5117985","name":"Recipes"}},{"@type":"ListI